<quantity box="[779,868,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. Variability of size in paratypes—females: 
<number box="[1352,1435,223,247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="5.75" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="5.7">5.7–5.8</number>
x 
<quantity box="[172,324,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2249999999999996" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.15" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="2.2249999999999996" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="2.15">2.15–2.3 mm</quantity>
; male: unknown. Body subcylindric, dark brown, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[961,1029,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1945,1968]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,339,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[161,1426,339,1921]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Habitus, dorsal view. 1. Deretus bezdeki sp. nov. (paratype), male; 2. D. bezdeki sp. nov. (paratype), female; 3. D. denticollis Gahan, 1900, male; 4. D. denticollis Gahan, 1900, female; 5. D. hulai sp. nov. (paratype), female; 6. D. maderai sp. nov. (holotype), male; 7. D. maderai sp. nov. (paratype), female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/211333/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1013,1029,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62" value="5.0">5</number>
